The HD 95544 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 95544 is a star with 1.09 times the mass of the Sun, and 1.09 times its radius. It is located 286.38 light years away from the solar system.

HD 95544 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 95544 system


HD 95544 b

HD 95544 b was discovered by the Haute-Provence Observatory observatory, in 2021-07, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 3.39 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 95544 b is 2175.120 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 95544 b is 12.700 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 95544 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
